Awesome! With the styled home page and navigation in place, now we'll add a database model for Projects. This lets you store project details (title, description, image, link) dynamically‚Äîno hardcoding in templates. We'll also set up Django's admin interface so you can easily add/edit projects via a web dashboard (superuser login).
This introduces Django's ORM (Object-Relational Mapping)‚Äîmodels define your data structure, and migrations apply changes to the DB.
4.1: Create the Project Model
Open portfolio_app/models.py and replace its content:
Pythonfrom django.db import models

class Project(models.Model):
    title = models.CharField(max_length=200)
    description = models.TextField()
    image = models.ImageField(upload_to='projects/', blank=True, null=True)  # Optional image
    link = models.URLField(blank=True, null=True)  # Optional external link
    created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)

    def __str__(self):
        return self.title

    class Meta:
        ordering = ['-created_at']  # Newest first

This defines a simple table: Each project has a title, desc, optional image/link, and auto-timestamp.

