5.1: Create the Contact Form

Create portfolio_app/forms.py (new file):Pythonfrom django import forms
from crispy_forms.helper import FormHelper
from crispy_forms.layout import Submit

class ContactForm(forms.Form):
    name = forms.CharField(max_length=100, label='Your Name')
    email = forms.EmailField(label='Your Email')
    message = forms.CharField(widget=forms.Textarea(attrs={'rows': 4}), label='Message')

    def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):
        super().__init__(*args, **kwargs)
        self.helper = FormHelper()
        self.helper.add_input(Submit('submit', 'Send Message', css_class='btn btn-primary'))
This defines a simple form with validation. Crispy handles the Bootstrap look.


